meanings.definition: The art or process of making prints, especially by engraving, etching, or lithography.
meanings.sent1: She studied printmakings in art class and learned how to create beautiful prints.
meanings.sent2: The museum displayed a collection of printmakings from different artists around the world.
meanings.sent3: The mischievous student accidentally spilled ink all over his printmakings project.
meanings.sent4: Her creativity flowed through her printmakings like a river of colors.
meanings.sent5: The intricate details in his printmakings brought the images to life on paper.

meanings.definition: The products or works produced by the process of making prints.
meanings.sent1: The gallery showcased a variety of unique printmakings created by local artists.
meanings.sent2: Collectors often seek rare and valuable printmakings to add to their collections.
meanings.sent3: The art store had a sale on printmakings, attracting many customers looking for new pieces.
meanings.sent4: Her room was filled with colorful printmakings that brightened up the space.
meanings.sent5: The exhibition featured modern printmakings that pushed the boundaries of traditional art.
